  <prompt>
    Per NFR-07, the standard `sprk_communication` form must remain available as an admin/debug fallback after task 038's Form Component Control swap. Document:
    1. How to switch back to the standard form WITHOUT code changes (form order toggle, security role assignment, or similar mechanism)
    2. Which admin role(s) currently have access to the standard form
    3. The step-by-step procedure for an admin to access a `sprk_communication` record via the standard form when needed (e.g., for troubleshooting a record the Code Page cannot display)

    Produce `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/039-admin-fallback-procedure.md`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke Dataverse administrator documentation author. Familiar with form security role assignment, form order management, and admin troubleshooting workflows.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Research note describing the admin fallback procedure: anyone with admin access can recover the standard `sprk_communication` form view without engineering involvement. NFR-07 reversibility documented.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 038 swapped the default form for the Code Page-bound form. NFR-07 binds R3 to keep the standard form accessible to admins as a debug/fallback. This task captures the operational procedure so the swap doesn't trap users when the Code Page is unavailable (e.g., during outage or for a record with corrupt data the Code Page can't render).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/039-admin-fallback-procedure.md (NEW)</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/038-form-swap-deploy.md (INPUT — task 038 deploy notes)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

