  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read task 038's deploy note to confirm the exact mechanism used (Form Component Control vs primary form replacement) and how standard form was retained.</step>
    <step order="2">Inventory admin security roles in dev environment with access to the standard form post-swap.</step>
    <step order="3">Document the toggle-back procedure:
      - Step 1: open the form order configuration (path in Maker portal)
      - Step 2: change form order or visibility flags
      - Step 3: publish customizations
      - Step 4: verify by opening a record
    </step>
    <step order="4">Document the admin-access procedure (without toggle):
      - Admins assigned the appropriate security role can navigate to a `sprk_communication` record and select the standard form from the form switcher dropdown (if available in the UI)
    </step>
    <step order="5">Write `notes/research/039-admin-fallback-procedure.md` with:
      - Summary
      - Toggle-back procedure (full reversibility)
      - Admin-access procedure (per-record fallback)
      - Security role inventory
      - Troubleshooting scenarios (when to use the fallback)
    </step>
    <step order="6">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 039 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed.</step>
  </steps>

